@NODE 0. "Preface"
Preface
~~~~~~~
    Since a few months, I use several startup-sequences, shell-startups and user-startups
for a better use of my Amiga. For example, if I need a lot of memory or if I want to
speed up my Amiga boot, ..., I change my startup-sequence file. With differents user-startups,
I can vary the number of assigns. Shell-startups provide me several programming 
environments (C, E or Java). That's why I've began to number all these files
(startup_sequence1, startup-sequence2, ...) and rename it in startup-sequence, 
user-startup and shell-startup when i want to use it ... I looked for a software
which can manage all the startup files but I didn't found any one :-( So I took my courage
in both hands and decided to program my own utility : StartMeUp was born on
January 2000.

                                                                     Glames of Boing Attitude.
@ENDNODE

